This paper deals with the optimization of HVAC systems using model predictive control, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The use of optimization techniques and prediction models also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The study involves the use of a building thermal simulator, which could be classified under computer engineering (cs.CE) or software engineering (cs.SE).
